OL,5, The mother of a disabled woman who     
OL,6, killed herself after her benefits were 
OL,7, cut has won a legal battle for a new   
OL,8, inquest into her daughter's death.     
OL,10,FJody Whiting, 42, from Stockton, died  
OL,11,Fin February 2017 - days after her      
OL,12,Fdisability benefits were stopped by the
OL,13,FDepartment for Work and Pensions (DWP).
OL,15,FA coroner ruled her death was suicide, 
OL,16,Fbut her mother, Joy Dove, wants a new  
OL,17,Finquest to look at the DWP's impact.   
OL,19,FThe judge said it was "desirable in the
OL,20,Finterests of justice".                 
